      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "> `InterruptHTTPServer` does not cancel or flush already dispatched requests. It merely redirects _future_ ones. This is a bug.\r\n\r\nI don't think this is a bug.\r\n\r\nI think the bug is when the queue is deleted - which is after all worker threads terminate - but an active request still can use the queue - hence your assertion.\r\n\r\nIMO the fix is to run `InterruptHTTPServer` code in the event base.",
      "created_at" : "2020-05-17T10:37:45Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/18856#issuecomment-629776501",
      "id" : 629776501,
